You have access to a generic HTTP tool for making requests to whitelisted API endpoints.

IMPORTANT: Always prefer dedicated toolsets when available:
- For Grafana: use grafana/* tools
- For Prometheus: use prometheus/* tools
- For Kubernetes: use kubernetes/* tools
- For Elasticsearch: use elasticsearch/* tools
- For other services with dedicated toolsets: use those first

Only use the http_request tool when:
1. No dedicated toolset exists for the API you need to access
2. The endpoint is configured in the HTTP toolset whitelist

The http_request tool supports:
- GET requests (default for most endpoints)
- POST requests (only on endpoints explicitly configured to allow POST)
- JSON response filtering with `jq` expressions and `max_depth`

## Common API Patterns

### Confluence (Atlassian)

Confluence supports two authentication methods with different URL patterns:

#### Method 1: Classic Auth (Personal API Tokens)
Use site-specific URLs with the instance name:
- URL pattern: `https://{instance}.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/{pageId}?expand=body.storage`
- Auth: Basic auth with email:token

Example: To fetch page 2424833 from robusta-llm-test.atlassian.net:
```
GET https://robusta-llm-test.atlassian.net/wiki/rest/api/content/2424833?expand=body.storage
```

#### Method 2: Service Account Auth (Scoped Tokens)
Use the api.atlassian.com gateway with cloudId:
- URL pattern: `https://api.atlassian.com/ex/confluence/{cloudId}/wiki/rest/api/content/{pageId}?expand=body.storage`
- Auth: Bearer token
- The cloudId is a UUID identifying the Confluence instance

Example: To fetch page 2424833 via gateway (cloudId = abc123):
```
GET https://api.atlassian.com/ex/confluence/abc123/wiki/rest/api/content/2424833?expand=body.storage
```

#### Common Notes
- Extract the page ID from the URL (the numeric ID in the path, e.g., `2424833` from `/pages/2424833/Page+Title`)
- If URL format is `/wiki/spaces/SPACE/pages/PAGEID/Title`, the page ID is the number after `/pages/`
- If URL format is `/wiki/display/SPACE/Title`, you need to search for the page first
- The `expand=body.storage` parameter returns the page content in storage format (HTML)
- Page content is in the response at `.body.storage.value`
- Check which host is whitelisted to determine which URL pattern to use

